rComments: Most challenging course in my undergrad, but also the most rewarding experience. You need to read a lot, know some important detail, but he will give you questions beforehand. He's very helpful in the office hours, both on course materials and essay expectations, feedback is super detail. You will learn a lot, but plz do the readings!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Professor Choen is easily one of the most inspirational professors at UTSC. He brought stimulating & well thought out lectures on a weekly basis that changes your perception of everything with regards to the environment. If you ever want to take a class that leaves your mind blown at the end, this is defiantly a class to take. Thank you prof Choen.

Loooooots of readings that you will be tested heavily upon, but his lectures are GREAT and he's very clear when explaining the material and what he wants. Sure, his class is kind of hard but put in the work and you can easily get an A. Engaging lectures, funny, and clearly passionate about the topic. Would for sure take a class with him again.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', 'Get ready to read', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Prof Cohen is super tough. Expects you to do tons of readings, know small details from them, marks hard and gives the marks back VERY slowly. Going into the final exam, we only had 30% of our class mark back. He doesn't provide slides which is inconvenient but he does give the exam questions beforehand. Lectures were kinda boring too.

Saul really changed my perspective on how I view the world. His lectures are interesting, provocative, and always has a surprise up his sleeve. The few reviewers on him possibly came in with a closed mindset reflecting the opposite of what this course teaches. Yes he guides you to a certain viewpoint, but it's to break the ingrained narrative.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: This course will completely change the way you see the world. It is a challenging course - pay attention and do the readings but it really pays off! He is very helpful. Best course I have ever taken. The people who rated him before me were probably the ones that sit at the back of the class playing on facebook on their laptops.

OMG- I cannot emphasize enough to avoid this guy, shy, slow, boring, hard class, odd ideas, tells you what to think rather than teaching you to think, yes the material is interesting but he over explains and a lot of it is just useless, a lot of random papers and  assignments, fairly okay marker, course is useless and so is the prof.

Based on initial lecture only, appears to severely underestimate the abilities of his students, and does not prepare enough material for lecture. Pace is very slow and slightly frustrating. Ideas are relevant and interesting, but dramatically over-explained and few and far between.
